    "plan_content": "Here's the plan I've prepared. It covers **8 distinct touch points** across the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**New command:** `uv cache stats [--human]`  \n**Output:** One line per cache bucket (10 buckets via `CacheBucket::iter()`), then a `Total` line. Column-aligned with a 24-char label width.\n\n### Files to touch\n\n| # | File | What changes |\n|---|------|--------------|\n| 1 | `crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs` | Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` feature flag with `as_str`/`from_str`/test entries |\n| 2 | `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + new `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct |\n| 3 | `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — the command implementation |\n| 4 | `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | `mod cache_stats;` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` |\n| 5 | `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Add `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` match arm |\n| 6 | `crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs` | Add `cache_stats()` command helper + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter helper |\n| 7 | `crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs` | Register `mod cache_stats` under `test-python + test-pypi` feature gate |\n| 8 | `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — 3 integration tests (empty/raw, with-packages/raw, with-packages/human) |\n\n### Key reuse\n- **`CacheBucket::iter()`** — already iterates all 10 active buckets in the right order\n- **`cache.bucket(bucket)`** — returns `PathBuf` per bucket\n- **`DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()`** — same `diskus` call used by `cache size`\n- **`human_readable_bytes()`** — same formatter used by `cache size --human`\n- **`CacheBucket: Display`** — already formats as the versioned dir name (e.g., `\"wheels-v6\"`)",
